              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>Most parameters are within normal limits. Mildly elevated potassium and chloride, with slightly decreased total CO₂, may suggest a tendency toward mild metabolic acidosis or early renal tubular dysfunction. Renal function (urea, creatinine) is normal. Recommend clinical correlation and, if indicated, repeat electrolytes and assess acid-base status.</td></tr></table></div>"
